	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />We have  a Defender cab, with a modified control panel with the Inviso button and a stargate boardset to play that, too. My dad just finished up his mod to play All the williams classics on one boardset with a couple new boards and a switch, he's building it soon. It played Defender on a Stargate set 100% perfectly and will work with everything else. No sinistar though, thats a different monitor and extra board so no sense in doing that. <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /> Nice cab. Great game, I was 7th in the world on Defender for XBLA before the arcade thing came, never got points so I never got the game there. I doubt my score transferred over. :/
<br />
<br />
<br />Have fun though! Our cabinet is beat to HELL and back, but Williams games are amazing, nomatter what the cabinet is like. When you get this thing running like a champ again it'll be a BLAST. Williams arcade games are amazing. I'd love to develop on a Williams arcade game, but my dad hasn't supplied me with a board set or time to develop on it. Has has all the registers mapped out, listed, what they do, etc. But has never wrote anything on it! The only thing I really know is the games first instruction is CLR D000. Reset the bankswitching. <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" />
<br />
<br />
<br />This is the best decision of your life. Sounds like the game needs alot of repair, but it's worth the time. Your never going to regret it! Keep us updated, the cab isn't that bad from the pics.

		

